I would reccomend reading one of the books by Phillip Pullman first. It does sound like a bit of a carbon copy, and the book isn't exactly unknown, you may find after reading a bit that it's too close for comfort, or you may decide you want to continue and it may spark some ideas. either way, it's a damn good book.... (it's fantasy, by the way)<br>
you MUST feel you can comitt to your idea or you'll get through five pages then give up. If unoriginality is a problem for you then you should change your idea. Me, i'm not fussed. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Everything's</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> been done before, you just need to give an old idea a new angle..<br>
